00:13:01.573 --> 00:13:05.785
Robert is. uh… How can I put this? Uh.
he's-he's used to getting what he wants.

233
00:13:05.786 --> 00:13:08.746
I mean. you-you've met him.
He's handsome. rich. spoiled.

234
00:13:08.747 --> 00:13:11.583
Lot of fancy education.
but sadly. not much to show for it.

235
00:13:12.417 --> 00:13:17.840
And so when things don't go his way…
Yeah. I've seen him. uh. react.

236
00:13:18.507 --> 00:13:21.384
- He wrote Nancy a letter.
- What letter?

237
00:13:21.385 --> 00:13:23.053
Robert knew about the affair.

238
00:13:23.637 --> 00:13:27.223
He pretended not to. but he did.

239
00:13:27.224 --> 00:13:31.979
And they got into a fight.
and Nancy was scared of him.

240
00:13:32.646 --> 00:13:34.605
So he had to write her an apology letter.

241
00:13:34.606 --> 00:13:36.441
Eleanor told me yesterday.

242
00:13:37.734 --> 00:13:38.735
I'll look into that.

243
00:13:39.403 --> 00:13:43.073
Have you looked
into Nancy's stepdad? Scott?

244
00:13:43.657 --> 00:13:45.157
You're referring to Mr. Reed?

245
00:13:45.158 --> 00:13:49.328
Yes. You are aware that he
assaulted her when she was a child?

246
00:13:49.329 --> 00:13:50.663
Have you checked into that?

247
00:13:50.664 --> 00:13:52.373
We've reached out to Mr. Reed

248
00:13:52.374 --> 00:13:55.168
and he informed us
that he's had no contact

249
00:13:55.169 --> 00:13:57.044
with Mrs. Hennessey in 20 years.

250
00:13:57.045 --> 00:13:58.671
Unless you know differently.

251
00:13:58.672 --> 00:14:00.924
All I know is that she was scared of him.

252
00:14:01.758 --> 00:14:04.635
She sketched him in this scrapbook
that she has.

253
00:14:04.636 --> 00:14:05.804
And she was… It's…

254
00:14:06.305 --> 00:14:07.806
It's clear she was scared of him.

255
00:14:09.183 --> 00:14:10.517
[Ganz clicks tongue] Okay.

256
00:14:11.518 --> 00:14:12.686
"Okay"? [stammers]

257
00:14:13.812 --> 00:14:16.647
These are things
that you can go off of. Detective. okay?

258
00:14:16.648 --> 00:14:18.567
One of these men killed my friend.

259
00:14:19.401 --> 00:14:21.069
What makes you so certain it was a man?

260
00:14:22.070 --> 00:14:23.487
- Are you…
- [stammers. sighs]

261
00:14:23.488 --> 00:14:26.449
Detective Ganz. my-my wife
has been pretty generous with her time.

262
00:14:26.450 --> 00:14:30.204
And that's appreciated. I just…
I have one more question.

263
00:14:31.205 --> 00:14:33.998
What time did you say
you left dinner that night?

264
00:14:33.999 --> 00:14:35.500
Like I said. about 9:00 or so.

265
00:14:35.501 --> 00:14:38.253
And if a bartender said he served you
three or four drinks

266
00:14:38.921 --> 00:14:41.882
after the ladies left. he would be lying?

267
00:14:42.966 --> 00:14:44.800
I may have stayed for a drink.

268
00:14:44.801 --> 00:14:48.638
He had told us that he needed to.
quote. "Pour you into an Uber."

269
00:14:48.639 --> 00:14:51.433
Is it possible there are parts
of that night you don't remember?

270
00:14:52.684 --> 00:14:55.269
My wife came home at 10:30
and went straight to bed.

271
00:14:55.270 --> 00:14:56.772
I was with her the whole night.

272
00:14:58.065 --> 00:15:00.984
- [Mary] Ooh! Oops. I can do it.
- Okay. [grunts] Okay.

273
00:15:05.364 --> 00:15:07.407
Now. do I need to call an attorney?

274
00:15:08.075 --> 00:15:10.244
Relax. We're done here.

275
00:15:28.554 --> 00:15:30.638
Is that the. uh… the scrapbook?

276
00:15:30.639 --> 00:15:33.099
- Mm-hmm.
- The one you mentioned to the detective?

277
00:15:33.100 --> 00:15:37.020
Yeah. You must've seen Nancy
doodling in rehearsal or something.

278
00:15:37.771 --> 00:15:40.565
Possibly. Have the cops seen it?

279
00:15:40.566 --> 00:15:42.150
Yeah. they didn't think it was useful.

280
00:15:43.360 --> 00:15:45.194
- Well. is it?
- Yeah. I think so.

281
00:15:45.195 --> 00:15:48.907
But you saw Detective Ganz blow me off
when I brought up the drawing.

282
00:15:49.491 --> 00:15:53.536
I just feel like if I could
find something definitive…

283
00:15:53.537 --> 00:15:55.329
To take suspicion off of Eleanor.

284
00:15:55.330 --> 00:15:57.374
I just want to know
what happened to Nancy.

285
00:16:01.253 --> 00:16:05.464
Well. I have a call set up
with the real estate agent in Ohio.

286
00:16:05.465 --> 00:16:06.884
Unless you think I should cancel it.

287
00:16:07.384 --> 00:16:09.468
[clicks tongue. sighs]

288
00:16:09.469 --> 00:16:12.598
No. No. [chuckling]

289
00:16:14.474 --> 00:16:16.143
- [chuckles]
- Now put that away.

290
00:16:16.727 --> 00:16:19.270
The. uh. detective
looked like she was on top of it.

291
00:16:19.271 --> 00:16:21.607
- [Mary sighs]
- Let her do her job. Hmm?

292
00:16:37.164 --> 00:16:38.165
[sighs]

293
00:16:43.962 --> 00:16:45.631
[sighs]

294
00:16:46.298 --> 00:16:49.092
Nancy. what are you trying to say to me?

295
00:16:49.760 --> 00:16:52.679
[Mary] <i>Mary could never
bring herself to believe in God.</i>

296
00:16:53.472 --> 00:16:56.849
<i>But in those rare.
electric moments of inflection.</i>

297
00:16:56.850 --> 00:17:01.230
<i>she was sure she could feel
some energetic force guiding her way.</i>

298
00:17:02.064 --> 00:17:06.984
<i>And on that warm June afternoon.
Mary felt that energy at work again.</i>

299
00:17:07.653 --> 00:17:09.029
<i>Or maybe it was Nancy.</i>

300
00:17:09.530 --> 00:17:11.072
<i>Or Adderall.</i>

301
00:17:11.073 --> 00:17:12.406
<i>But it worked.</i>

302
00:17:28.131 --> 00:17:29.216
[gasps]

303
00:17:38.976 --> 00:17:40.811
[breathing shakily]

304
00:18:15.929 --> 00:18:18.890
[Howard] <i>"Give me a thousand kisses.
then a hundred.</i>

305
00:18:18.891 --> 00:18:21.893
<i>then a second thousand.
then a second hundred.</i>

306
00:18:21.894 --> 00:18:24.604
<i>Then another thousand.
and yet another hundred."</i>

307
00:18:24.605 --> 00:18:28.734
"You will give me
a thousand-thousand kisses.

308
00:18:29.484 --> 00:18:31.153
then we will both forget the count.

309
00:18:31.904 --> 00:18:37.242
So that no lonely man might grow jealous
when he learns the plenty of our love."

310
00:18:38.076 --> 00:18:42.581
Your mastery of ancient languages
is just… It's truly inspiring.

311
00:18:43.332 --> 00:18:49.963
Tiny thing. I think "conturbo" is more
"to confuse" than "to forget."

312
00:18:57.262 --> 00:19:00.181
[exhales deeply]

313
00:19:00.182 --> 00:19:02.934
- Jenny and I are over.
- Does she know that?

314
00:19:02.935 --> 00:19:04.102
She's a sick woman.

315
00:19:05.771 --> 00:19:09.023
And I… I hate to say it.
but she doesn't need a husband.

316
00:19:09.024 --> 00:19:10.359
She needs a doctor.

317
00:19:11.527 --> 00:19:13.946
When she's more stable. then I'll end it.

318
00:19:17.407 --> 00:19:18.408
[pen clicks]

319
00:19:26.250 --> 00:19:27.959
- Hi. Jenny.
- Mary. is he in there?

320
00:19:27.960 --> 00:19:29.086
Mm-hmm.

321
00:19:55.362 --> 00:19:58.115
Great. Send those listings over
so I can discuss with my wife.

322
00:19:58.615 --> 00:20:00.200
Thank you. Rita. You're a saint.

323
00:20:01.952 --> 00:20:03.953
Somebody might be
getting their own office.

324
00:20:03.954 --> 00:20:05.581
I found this in Nancy's scrapbook.

325
00:20:08.584 --> 00:20:09.835
What is it?

326
00:20:10.502 --> 00:20:13.046
It's a page from your <i>Catullus</i>.

327
00:20:13.714 --> 00:20:14.923
Okay. what am I looking at?

328
00:20:15.591 --> 00:20:17.843
The same line has been underlined.

329
00:20:19.636 --> 00:20:20.637
It's a good line.

330
00:20:21.388 --> 00:20:25.975
Howard. how did Nancy get ahold
of your obscure translation

331
00:20:25.976 --> 00:20:27.685
of an ancient Roman poet?

332
00:20:27.686 --> 00:20:29.145
I don't know. It's-It's on Amazon.

333
00:20:29.146 --> 00:20:32.607
It had a print run of basically zero.
No one… No one read the book.

334
00:20:32.608 --> 00:20:34.735
I don't know. Maybe I gave her a copy.
I don't remember.

335
00:20:41.491 --> 00:20:43.827
You gave Nancy a book of poetry?

336
00:20:45.495 --> 00:20:46.747
[smacks lips] Yeah.

337
00:20:47.331 --> 00:20:52.168
Yeah. we were. uh. talking at rehearsal
and the conversation turned to my work.

338
00:20:52.169 --> 00:20:53.711
and. uh. I said I'd bring her a copy.

339
00:20:53.712 --> 00:20:54.837
I'm surprised she read it.

340
00:20:54.838 --> 00:20:55.922
Mary. are you okay?

341
00:20:55.923 --> 00:20:57.673
Just tell me what's going on. Howard.

342
00:20:57.674 --> 00:20:59.342
I could ask you the same question.

343
00:20:59.343 --> 00:21:01.345
Why did you give this to her?

344
00:21:05.432 --> 00:21:08.310
Mary. your pupils are like saucers.

345
00:21:09.061 --> 00:21:11.812
We've been down this road before.
I thought we were past this.

346
00:21:11.813 --> 00:21:13.397
Are you using those pills again?

347
00:21:13.398 --> 00:21:14.815
You're deflecting. You're not…

348
00:21:14.816 --> 00:21:16.943
Mary. we don't want to lose control again.

349
00:21:16.944 --> 00:21:19.320
Remember what happened
last time you spun out?

350
00:21:19.321 --> 00:21:20.655
How scared we were?

351
00:21:20.656 --> 00:21:23.616
- No. this is… No. this is different.
- You put our kids in danger.

352
00:21:23.617 --> 00:21:26.745
Thank God Junie was okay.
We might not get so lucky next time.

353
00:21:42.010 --> 00:21:45.012
[Mary] <i>Mary turned it over
and over in her mind.</i>

354
00:21:45.013 --> 00:21:49.016
<i>She tried to see it from every angle.
and none of them made sense.</i>

355
00:21:49.017 --> 00:21:52.479
<i>Nancy and Howard. Howard and Nancy.</i>

356
00:21:54.106 --> 00:21:57.149
<i>Howard looked
completely unfamiliar to Mary.</i>

357
00:21:57.150 --> 00:22:00.737
<i>But also exactly the same.
like a Howard forgery.</i>

358
00:22:03.365 --> 00:22:05.325
<i>Was that always how he smelled?</i>

359
00:22:07.870 --> 00:22:10.789
[dramatic music playing]

360
00:22:30.309 --> 00:22:31.310
[sighs]

361
00:22:33.312 --> 00:22:35.188
[breathes deeply]

362
00:22:35.189 --> 00:22:37.524
[Mary] <i>Had Nancy been counterfeit too?</i>

363
00:22:38.901 --> 00:22:41.069
<i>Who was the real Nancy Hennessey?</i>

364
00:22:50.913 --> 00:22:52.623
<i>That fucking ballet.</i>

365
00:22:54.374 --> 00:22:55.458
<i>That night.</i>

366
00:22:55.459 --> 00:22:59.462
[ominous music plays]

367
00:22:59.463 --> 00:23:01.381
[Mary] <i>She should've known that night.</i>

368
00:23:16.438 --> 00:23:18.524
<i>Mary should've talked to Howard then…</i>

369
00:23:20.275 --> 00:23:21.359
[door slams]

370
00:23:21.360 --> 00:23:23.946
<i>…but he was in one of his moods.</i>

371
00:23:26.532 --> 00:23:28.574
[line ringing]

372
00:23:28.575 --> 00:23:30.702
[Mary] <i>It was Nancy who looked distraught.</i>

373
00:23:33.038 --> 00:23:34.705
<i>You've reached Nancy Hennessey.</i>

374
00:23:34.706 --> 00:23:36.999
<i>I'm unavailable to take your call
at the moment.</i>

375
00:23:37.000 --> 00:23:40.003
[Mary] <i>And concern
makes a fine excuse for curiosity.</i>

376
00:24:10.450 --> 00:24:11.617
[crying]

377
00:24:11.618 --> 00:24:13.077
[Mary] <i>The tears were real.</i>

378
00:24:13.078 --> 00:24:15.247
- [knocks on door]
- [gasps. breathes shakily] Mary?

379
00:24:16.707 --> 00:24:18.749
- [Mary] <i>Everything else was a lie.</i>
- Hey.

380
00:24:18.750 --> 00:24:21.711
- <i>Right to Mary's face.</i>
- Hey. It's okay. It's okay.

381
00:24:21.712 --> 00:24:23.880
- [sniffles]
- It's okay.

382
00:24:23.881 --> 00:24:26.215
[Nancy]
When Robert drinks. he's someone else.

383
00:24:26.216 --> 00:24:29.427
I don't know what set him off tonight.
but I just knew I had to get out of there.

384
00:24:29.428 --> 00:24:30.971
I didn't have a plan. I just drove.

385
00:24:33.182 --> 00:24:36.894
Why did you go to Howard
and not me or Eleanor? [chuckles]

386
00:24:38.604 --> 00:24:40.314
I didn't want you to hate Robert.

387
00:24:42.107 --> 00:24:43.441
I mean. Howard already does.

388
00:24:43.442 --> 00:24:47.154
Plus he has experience with… you know.

389
00:24:50.824 --> 00:24:54.118
Come on. it's not like
I was strung out on heroin.

390
00:24:54.119 --> 00:24:56.162
I needed a few extra hours of energy.

391
00:24:56.163 --> 00:24:59.624
- We all did it in college.
- No. I know. I know. I'm…

392
00:24:59.625 --> 00:25:02.293
Howard wasn't much help at all. anyway.

393
00:25:02.294 --> 00:25:05.713
I mean… You know. desperate times.

394
00:25:05.714 --> 00:25:07.715
So are you gonna go home?

395
00:25:07.716 --> 00:25:09.384
Like. ever? I hope so.

396
00:25:10.469 --> 00:25:12.261
Why don't you come crash with us tonight?

397
00:25:12.262 --> 00:25:13.387
- No.
- Yeah.

398
00:25:13.388 --> 00:25:15.389
No. no. no. no. Um. no. I…

399
00:25:15.390 --> 00:25:17.725
I'll probably just…
I'll just go to Ojai. I think.

400
00:25:17.726 --> 00:25:19.060
'Kay.

401
00:25:19.061 --> 00:25:21.480
[breathes deeply]

402
00:25:22.689 --> 00:25:25.691
Mare. today started out so perfectly.
And then it just…

403
00:25:25.692 --> 00:25:28.319
And then it ended with you
and your best friend

404
00:25:28.320 --> 00:25:32.073
gorging themselves
on the entire Norm's hot cake menu.

405
00:25:32.074 --> 00:25:34.618
That's what you're going to remember
about tonight. right?

406
00:25:35.327 --> 00:25:38.079
Good. Well. we have
some more work to do. so…

407
00:25:38.080 --> 00:25:41.207
Sir. can we see
that hot cakes menu please?

408
00:25:41.208 --> 00:25:44.836
[Mary] <i>And sweet Mary.
our lady of the tender. bleeding heart.</i>

409
00:25:44.837 --> 00:25:47.005
<i>she actually believed that horseshit.</i>

410
00:25:49.049 --> 00:25:51.175
Hey. sweetheart. What're you doing up?

411
00:25:51.176 --> 00:25:52.552
I couldn't sleep.

412
00:25:52.553 --> 00:25:55.514
[Mary] Uh-oh. You could sleep
through the second coming.

413
00:25:57.224 --> 00:25:58.307
Yeah. it's nothing.

414
00:25:58.308 --> 00:25:59.935
All right. What kind of nothing?

415
00:26:02.896 --> 00:26:04.356
First. promise you won't get mad.

416
00:26:05.899 --> 00:26:07.025
I cross my heart.

417
00:26:08.694 --> 00:26:09.695
[sighs]

418
00:26:10.487 --> 00:26:13.615
It's Aunt Eleanor.
I heard what that detective said today.

419
00:26:14.908 --> 00:26:15.992
You were listening?

420
00:26:15.993 --> 00:26:19.329
I know the cops think
she killed Aunt Nancy. and…

421
00:26:21.957 --> 00:26:23.083
I know she didn't.

422
00:26:27.588 --> 00:26:29.047
How do you know that. Marcus?

423
00:26:29.673 --> 00:26:31.383
'Cause the night Nancy died…

424
00:26:33.468 --> 00:26:34.927
she-she was with me.

425
00:26:34.928 --> 00:26:36.220
Who was?

426
00:26:36.221 --> 00:26:39.391
Eleanor. She came to get me in Van Nuys.

427
00:26:40.100 --> 00:26:41.518
What were you doing in Van Nuys?

428
00:26:42.978 --> 00:26:45.479
Yeah. I know it was dumb to go.
but I owed this kid some money and he…

429
00:26:45.480 --> 00:26:46.856
he said we could figure something out.

430
00:26:46.857 --> 00:26:48.566
Damn it. Marcus. You're gambling again?

431
00:26:48.567 --> 00:26:50.735
I only did it so I wouldn't have to
ask you guys for cash.

432
00:26:50.736 --> 00:26:51.819
What?

433
00:26:51.820 --> 00:26:53.571
You and Dad are always
so worried about money.

434
00:26:53.572 --> 00:26:56.575
- You are on probation. Do you understand…
- Mom. Okay. Mom. You promised.

435
00:26:57.159 --> 00:27:00.453
[breathes deeply] Mm-hmm.

436
00:27:00.454 --> 00:27:02.455
They wouldn't let me leave
until I paid up.

437
00:27:02.456 --> 00:27:07.043
Oh. my God. [gasps. sighs]
So you called Eleanor?

438
00:27:07.044 --> 00:27:09.045
She's the only person I know
with that kind of cash.

439
00:27:09.046 --> 00:27:10.630
She paid your bookie?

440
00:27:10.631 --> 00:27:15.177
The cops think she killed Aunt Nancy.
and I… I'm her only alibi.

441
00:27:15.969 --> 00:27:17.220
She's protecting you.

442
00:27:17.221 --> 00:27:20.014
I seriously don't know what would've
happened that night if she hadn't come.

443
00:27:20.015 --> 00:27:22.016
But I can't let her get in trouble. and…

444
00:27:22.017 --> 00:27:23.017
Sweetie.

445
00:27:23.018 --> 00:27:25.311
- I just… I don't know what to do.
- Sweetie. it's okay.

446
00:27:25.312 --> 00:27:28.856
- Mom. I don't know what to do. [crying]
- Come here. come here. It's okay.

447
00:27:28.857 --> 00:27:31.275
I just don't want you and Aunt Ellie
to stop being friends 'cause of me.

448
00:27:31.276 --> 00:27:34.154
Oh. we're never gonna stop being friends.

449
00:27:35.531 --> 00:27:37.949
We have been through too much already…

450
00:27:37.950 --> 00:27:39.659
- Yeah. Yeah. [sniffles]
- …her and I. Right?

451
00:27:39.660 --> 00:27:42.162
You're a good man. you know that?

452
00:27:43.413 --> 00:27:45.373
Just please call me next time. okay?

453
00:27:45.374 --> 00:27:47.124
I know. I was gonna tell you
when I got home.

454
00:27:47.125 --> 00:27:50.170
It's just… You were asleep
and-and Dad wasn't home.

455
00:27:51.213 --> 00:27:52.214
What do you…

456
00:27:53.090 --> 00:27:54.465
Where was Dad?

457
00:27:54.466 --> 00:27:56.885
I don't know.
His car wasn't in the driveway.

458
00:28:06.186 --> 00:28:08.438
- Mom?
- Sorry. it's all right. Just. um…

459
00:28:09.898 --> 00:28:11.858
Why don't you go get some sleep. okay?

460
00:28:11.859 --> 00:28:14.736
[sniffles] We'll talk about it tomorrow.
It's okay.

461
00:28:27.791 --> 00:28:29.459
Howard's been lying about everything.

462
00:28:38.969 --> 00:28:41.013
He told the cops he was home.

463
00:28:44.558 --> 00:28:45.893
When did he leave?

464
00:28:52.608 --> 00:28:53.984
He was wearing that blazer.

465
00:28:56.862 --> 00:28:59.448
[suspenseful music playing]

466
00:29:46.370 --> 00:29:48.997
[breathing heavily]

467
00:30:31.498 --> 00:30:33.541
Are you wearing your
claddagh ring I gave you?

468
00:30:33.542 --> 00:30:35.877
You told me it would be
my grounding force. right?

469
00:30:35.878 --> 00:30:38.255
[suspenseful music continues]

470
00:30:47.931 --> 00:30:51.185
[breathing shakily]

471
00:30:57.441 --> 00:30:59.401
You look mad. Are you mad?

472
00:30:59.902 --> 00:31:03.447
Yes. I am mad… at you. Nancy. [pants]

473
00:31:04.656 --> 00:31:08.202
Did our friendship mean so little to you?

474
00:31:08.869 --> 00:31:10.494
How could you do this to me?

475
00:31:10.495 --> 00:31:11.997
[Nancy] Well. you did it too.

476
00:31:12.664 --> 00:31:14.124
To Howard's wife.

477
00:31:15.334 --> 00:31:16.335
[breathing heavily]

478
00:31:17.878 --> 00:31:21.756
What? No. that was
completely different. [sighs]

479
00:31:21.757 --> 00:31:22.966
[Nancy] How?

480
00:31:28.889 --> 00:31:31.225
[suspenseful music continues]

481
00:31:34.895 --> 00:31:35.896
[sighs]

482
00:31:54.373 --> 00:31:55.791
[tires screech]

483
00:32:18.021 --> 00:32:20.357
[dog barking]

484
00:32:34.830 --> 00:32:35.831
Who's there?

485
00:32:36.832 --> 00:32:37.875
Jenny?

486
00:32:38.709 --> 00:32:39.834
Do I know you?

487
00:32:39.835 --> 00:32:40.836
It's Mary.

488
00:32:41.879 --> 00:32:43.255
Mary McCormack.

489
00:32:46.508 --> 00:32:48.177
Oh. my God. Mary. [sighs]

490
00:32:50.429 --> 00:32:54.558
- I'm sorry to barge in on you like this.
- [sighs] How did you find me?

491
00:32:55.475 --> 00:32:59.104
Um. I follow you on Facebook.
which is embarrassing to admit.

492
00:32:59.938 --> 00:33:02.024
Did Howard send you?
Does he know where I live?

493
00:33:02.691 --> 00:33:03.942
He doesn't know I'm here.

494
00:33:17.539 --> 00:33:18.624
[clears throat]

495
00:33:21.043 --> 00:33:22.044
[sighs]

496
00:33:23.086 --> 00:33:24.338
What happened. Mary?

497
00:33:24.922 --> 00:33:27.174
Um. I'm really doing it.

498
00:33:28.091 --> 00:33:29.968
When you and Howard were…

499
00:33:30.969 --> 00:33:32.386
No. what am I trying to say?

500
00:33:32.387 --> 00:33:36.641
Um. when you and Howard
first started dating…

501
00:33:36.642 --> 00:33:40.979
[breathes deeply] …did he read you poetry?

502
00:33:41.730 --> 00:33:42.940
That's your question?

503
00:33:45.067 --> 00:33:46.151
[breathes deeply]

504
00:33:47.194 --> 00:33:49.905
I need you to help me understand.

505
00:33:54.076 --> 00:33:56.703
No. that's just… I'm sorry. that's insane.

506
00:33:57.496 --> 00:33:58.955
Oh. I sound insane.

507
00:33:58.956 --> 00:34:00.582
You don't owe me anything.

508
00:34:01.291 --> 00:34:05.254
'Cause your husband left you for me.
so you probably hate me.

509
00:34:07.005 --> 00:34:08.756
That's what he told you?

510
00:34:08.757 --> 00:34:10.050
That he left?

511
00:34:11.134 --> 00:34:13.594
Yes. yes. [sighs]

512
00:34:14.721 --> 00:34:16.805
When I got pregnant. he divorced you. so…

513
00:34:16.806 --> 00:34:17.808
Wow.

514
00:34:19.476 --> 00:34:20.978
Do you want to know the truth?

515
00:34:28.777 --> 00:34:31.655
The truth is that you weren't
the first of his co-eds.

516
00:34:32.364 --> 00:34:33.532
but you were different.

517
00:34:34.074 --> 00:34:35.324
You sought me out.

518
00:34:35.826 --> 00:34:39.870
You were this brilliant. young woman
with a stunning career ahead of you.

519
00:34:39.871 --> 00:34:41.998
And stupid me.
I thought I could guide you.

520
00:34:44.126 --> 00:34:46.961
I let you into my life and all along.

521
00:34:46.962 --> 00:34:49.839
you were just using me
to get closer to him.

522
00:34:49.840 --> 00:34:51.717
No. Jenny. That is not true.

523
00:34:52.676 --> 00:34:54.511
I respected you so much.

524
00:34:55.929 --> 00:34:58.849
and your work inspired me
to get into the field.

525
00:34:59.474 --> 00:35:01.268
And into my husband's bed.

526
00:35:05.772 --> 00:35:08.650
When I found out about you.
I told him I was done.

527
00:35:10.444 --> 00:35:12.112
He begged me not to go.

528
00:35:13.405 --> 00:35:18.492
[sighs] He called you
just another meaningless fling.

529
00:35:18.493 --> 00:35:24.041
And he said that he would refuse to
acknowledge the baby if I agreed to stay.

530
00:35:26.585 --> 00:35:29.588
No. he said… He said you were unstable.

531
00:35:30.088 --> 00:35:31.715
Did I seem unstable?

532
00:35:33.634 --> 00:35:38.096
You chose to believe him
over your own eyes.

533
00:35:38.931 --> 00:35:40.474
What else did he tell you?

534
00:35:41.391 --> 00:35:45.187
[swallows] He told me you cut your wrists.

535
00:35:45.938 --> 00:35:47.647
that you tried to kill yourself.

536
00:35:47.648 --> 00:35:48.941
[scoffs]

537
00:35:56.448 --> 00:35:58.200
But he did leave me with this.

538
00:35:59.660 --> 00:36:01.328
This is two flights of stairs.

539
00:36:01.912 --> 00:36:04.039
It was the night I told him I was leaving.

540
00:36:04.540 --> 00:36:05.791
We got into an argument.

541
00:36:07.292 --> 00:36:10.587
Howard can't fathom being left.

542
00:36:11.463 --> 00:36:13.549
I thought about you a lot over the years.

543
00:36:14.550 --> 00:36:16.510
I wondered how things turned out for you.

544
00:36:19.346 --> 00:36:20.973
I could've warned you about him.

545
00:36:23.267 --> 00:36:24.726
I wouldn't have believed you.

546
00:36:26.186 --> 00:36:27.688
What did Howard do to you?

547
00:36:29.189 --> 00:36:32.109
[sniffles. breathes shakily]

548
00:36:37.990 --> 00:36:41.243
[breathes shakily]

549
00:36:46.164 --> 00:36:47.165
[knocks on door]

550
00:36:53.797 --> 00:36:56.049
[breathing heavily. sniffles]

551
00:36:57.301 --> 00:37:01.138
I know who David is. [breathes heavily]

552
00:37:02.097 --> 00:37:06.268
I've always thought this poem
was a part of our story and now…

553
00:37:07.186 --> 00:37:11.898
I don't even know if it was ever mine
to begin with.

554
00:37:11.899 --> 00:37:14.692
Mary. he… He is a predator.

555
00:37:14.693 --> 00:37:17.112
I keep imagining him reading it to Nancy.

556
00:37:18.488 --> 00:37:24.243
I mean. clearly it was important to her.
She tore it out. She kept it.

557
00:37:24.244 --> 00:37:29.207
Maybe there was some part of her
that knew one day you would find it.

558
00:37:29.208 --> 00:37:31.042
She must've thought I was so stupid.

559
00:37:31.043 --> 00:37:32.627
- No.
- Which I am.

560
00:37:32.628 --> 00:37:35.631
- God. Do you have any Advil or anything?
- Yeah.

561
00:37:36.673 --> 00:37:42.595
You are not stupid. There is no reason
you should have known about this.

562
00:37:42.596 --> 00:37:45.223
Oh. come on. He did it to Jenny.

563
00:37:45.224 --> 00:37:46.849
Why wouldn't he do it to me?

564
00:37:46.850 --> 00:37:48.727
I just don't want you blaming yourself.

565
00:37:52.648 --> 00:37:54.399
- There were others.
- What do you mean?

566
00:37:57.152 --> 00:37:58.987
There were other women.

567
00:37:59.988 --> 00:38:01.614
You never said anything.

568
00:38:01.615 --> 00:38:02.990
What would have been the point?

569
00:38:02.991 --> 00:38:04.910
I was never gonna leave him.

570
00:38:05.410 --> 00:38:07.329
I would never do that to the kids.

571
00:38:08.038 --> 00:38:10.623
[sighs] And he always came back. you know?

572
00:38:10.624 --> 00:38:14.586
I… He needed me. I needed him
and that is all that mattered.

573
00:38:15.587 --> 00:38:18.047
There was one time
about five or six years ago

574
00:38:18.048 --> 00:38:20.925
when I was giving the girls a bath
and a woman came to the door.

575
00:38:20.926 --> 00:38:25.596
She was young. early 20s. You know. thin.

576
00:38:25.597 --> 00:38:28.433
And Howard said she was a grad student
who was upset about a grade.

577
00:38:29.309 --> 00:38:32.729
Took her up to his office.
closed the door. [sniffles]

578
00:38:33.522 --> 00:38:34.731
What did you do?

579
00:38:36.358 --> 00:38:37.985
I finished the bath. [chuckles]

580
00:38:41.905 --> 00:38:43.448
I never said a word about it.

581
00:38:44.157 --> 00:38:47.201
You were protecting yourself
and your family.

582
00:38:47.202 --> 00:38:52.164
But if I had said something then…
Nancy may still be alive.

583
00:38:52.165 --> 00:38:53.958
Okay. but you might not be.

584
00:38:53.959 --> 00:38:58.296
God. This ring. he took it off her body.

585
00:38:58.297 --> 00:38:59.338
Oh. Jesus.

586
00:38:59.339 --> 00:39:03.426
Ellie. Howard took it
off of her dead body.

587
00:39:03.427 --> 00:39:06.679
How is any of this real?
None of my life seems real.

588
00:39:06.680 --> 00:39:07.723
No. Listen to me.

589
00:39:08.891 --> 00:39:11.643
You and I are real.

590
00:39:12.269 --> 00:39:13.270
This is real.

591
00:39:15.689 --> 00:39:16.982
You needed me

592
00:39:18.692 --> 00:39:21.777
and I kicked you out of my home.
I am sorry.

593
00:39:21.778 --> 00:39:25.114
I should not have lied to you
about Robert.

594
00:39:25.115 --> 00:39:28.201
- No. Marcus told me what you did.
- [chuckles]

595
00:39:28.202 --> 00:39:33.247
You are risking your freedom
to protect my son? Why?

596
00:39:33.248 --> 00:39:34.457
Are you kidding me?

597
00:39:34.458 --> 00:39:39.003
That is my kid.
I was in the room when he was born.

598
00:39:39.004 --> 00:39:42.132
There is nothing I wouldn't do
to keep him safe.

599
00:39:42.841 --> 00:39:45.468
I know. I know you would.

600
00:39:45.469 --> 00:39:46.929
[groans. breathes shakily]

601
00:39:47.429 --> 00:39:48.846
[phone buzzes]

602
00:39:48.847 --> 00:39:50.015
- [gasps] Ellie.
- What?

603
00:39:50.516 --> 00:39:53.435
It's him. Oh. God.
I left my phone at the house.

604
00:39:55.395 --> 00:39:56.396
What should I do?

605
00:39:56.980 --> 00:39:58.564
- Answer it.
- Okay.

606
00:39:58.565 --> 00:40:01.193
- And you have to find out what he knows.
- Okay.

607
00:40:03.654 --> 00:40:04.737
Hello?

608
00:40:04.738 --> 00:40:06.698
[Howard] <i>Eleanor. where is she?
Where's Mary?</i>

609
00:40:07.199 --> 00:40:09.617
What? I don't… I don't know
what you're talking about. Howard.

610
00:40:09.618 --> 00:40:11.118
It's the middle of the night.

611
00:40:11.119 --> 00:40:14.831
[Howard] <i>I need to talk to her right now.
It's Artemis. She's in the hospital.</i>

612
00:40:20.462 --> 00:40:22.631
[Eleanor] Okay. they said room eight.

613
00:40:25.175 --> 00:40:27.385
[machines beeping]

614
00:40:27.386 --> 00:40:29.637
Oh. my God. Artie. sweetie. Mommy's here.

615
00:40:29.638 --> 00:40:31.265
What happened to her? What happened?

616
00:40:31.849 --> 00:40:33.641
Ma'am. you need to give us space.

617
00:40:33.642 --> 00:40:35.977
- Mary. let them do their job.
- [scoffs] She needs me.

618
00:40:35.978 --> 00:40:38.187
Please. somebody tell me what's going on.

619
00:40:38.188 --> 00:40:39.981
Over here.
We're trying to stabilize her now.

620
00:40:39.982 --> 00:40:41.148
- Okay.
- What?

621
00:40:41.149 --> 00:40:42.692
Your husband said
she swallowed some pills.

622
00:40:42.693 --> 00:40:44.527
- What pills?
- They were in this.

623
00:40:44.528 --> 00:40:46.196
- Do you recognize it?
- [sighs]

624
00:40:46.697 --> 00:40:47.698
What were the pills?

625
00:40:48.282 --> 00:40:50.700
Mom. you have to tell us
so we know how to help your daughter.

626
00:40:50.701 --> 00:40:55.496
It's. uh… [swallows] …Adderall. Uh.
ten milligrams. I think. It's Adderall.

627
00:40:55.497 --> 00:40:56.915
[nurse] Adderall. ten milligrams.

628
00:40:57.749 --> 00:40:59.417
- Mary…
- [nurse] Pulse is climbing.

629
00:40:59.418 --> 00:41:02.044
- 145. 160.
- [machines beeping]

630
00:41:02.045 --> 00:41:04.297
What's happening? What's… What's going on?

631
00:41:04.298 --> 00:41:05.340
What's happening? Is she okay?

632
00:41:06.091 --> 00:41:07.550
Artie. Mommy's here. okay?

633
00:41:07.551 --> 00:41:08.968
Mom. we need you to back up.

634
00:41:08.969 --> 00:41:11.095
Artie. Mommy's here.
I'm right here. sweetie.

635
00:41:11.096 --> 00:41:12.221
Your mommy's right here.

636
00:41:12.222 --> 00:41:13.764
It's gonna be okay. sweetie.

637
00:41:13.765 --> 00:41:16.267
[sniffles] Mommy's here. sweetie.
Mommy's right here.

638
00:41:16.268 --> 00:41:18.019
It's gonna be okay. [sniffles]

639
00:41:18.020 --> 00:41:20.438
[sobs] What's happening to my baby?

640
00:41:20.439 --> 00:41:25.319
[sniffles] Please help her. Please. [sobs]

641
00:41:26.305 --> 00:42:26.592
